### Hi.
I'm a Peruvian developer interested in programming, Linux, Hacking and AI. I tackle on challenging problems and try to solve them with code. If you want to know more about me here is my cv.

### About
My name is Jean Alesi Reynoso, I have 20 years and live in Lima, I'm a programmer who has over 4 years of experience in software development. I am currently working at Wunderman phantasia as a gardener(it's a joke!, work like Full stack developer).

### Creating pages manually
If you prefer to not use the automatic generator, push a branch named `gh-pages` to your repository to create a page manually. In addition to supporting regular HTML content, GitHub Pages support Jekyll, a simple, blog aware static site generator. Jekyll makes it easy to create site-wide headers and footers without having to copy them across every page. It also offers intelligent blog support and other advanced templating features.
note: Don't delete this file! It's used internally to help with page regeneration.
